"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-10-broken-marathon-legend-eliud-kipchoge-forced-take-taxi-olympic-finish-line-21399343\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Marathonlegend Eliud Kipchoge was forced to pull out of the Olympic race and suffered the ignominy of being forced to take a taxi ride to the finish line.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 29, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 39-year-old had been targeting an unprecedented third straight Olympic title but the veteran looked uncomfortable throughout the early stages of the race and never settled into his customary rhythm.\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipchoge made it to the 31-kilometer mark before eventually calling it quits and allowing last-placed Ser-Od Bat-Ochir to overtake him.\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At that point, the Kenyan handed his shoes and socks to two lucky supporters before disappearing into a vehicle which drove him to the finish line.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the race, a visibly emotional Kipchoge said: 'It is a difficult time for me.\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is my worst marathon.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have never done a DNF (did not finish).\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's life.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Like a boxer, I have been knocked down, I have won, I have come second, eighth, 10th, fifth - now I did not finish.\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's life.'\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 942, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On his future, the Kenyan said: 'I do not know what to do next.\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I need to go back [home], sit down, and try to figure out my 21 years of running at a high level.\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I need to evolve and feature in other things.'\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eliud Kipchoge at 31k, dropping out after waiting for last-place Ser-Od Bat-Ochirpic.twitter.com/qzGvYA0F8u  Great Britain's Emile Cairess, meanwhile, finished strongly to claim an impressive fourth place in a race won by Ethiopia's Tamirat Tola in an Olympic record.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}, {\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999133657546976, \"rank\": 6.316581820114632e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999949395588176, \"rank\": 5.008754240550119e-06, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tamirat Tola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tola took the title in a time of two hours six minutes and 26 seconds, winning his country's first gold of the Games.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"score\": 0.9999997355239779, \"rank\": 2.6040922495005336e-07, \"text\": \"Tola\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgian Bashir Abdi took the silver in 2:06.47 with the bronze going to Kenyan Benson Kipruto in 2:07.00.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999653439970582, \"rank\": 1.7637965328834267e-05, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bashir Abdi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\"}, {\"begin\": 1621, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Benson Kipruto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cairess, who qualified for the Paris Olympics after finishing third in the London Marathon in April, took fourth in 2:07.29.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tola, a bronze medallist in the 10,000m at Rio 2016, said: 'I am happy because I fulfilled my goal.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"score\": 0.9999997355239779, \"rank\": 2.6040922495005336e-07, \"text\": \"Tola\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I prepared well.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I trained hard so I could win.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In my life, this is my great achievement.'\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tola, who won the New York City marathon in a course record time last year, was not originally in the Ethiopian Olympic squad and was only drafted in when Sisay Lemma pulled out due to a hamstring injury.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York City marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.8694905556711624, \"rank\": 0.15009874849336027, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisay_Lemma\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sisay Lemma\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisay_Lemma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisay_Lemma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tola added: 'I was fully prepared and knew I could fulfil my dream.\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"score\": 0.9999997355239779, \"rank\": 2.6040922495005336e-07, \"text\": \"Tola\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuul_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am happy to do that.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the Olympics and it is not easy to win the Olympic Games, not at all.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am very proud, very happy.'\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cairess sat in second spot after 30km before dropping back but he overtook Ethiopia's Deresa Geleta and Akira Akasaki to finish fourth.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999949395588176, \"rank\": 5.008754240550119e-06, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akira_Nogami\", \"score\": 0.9999999965125426, \"rank\": 3.487657379114436e-09, \"text\": \"Akira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akira_Nogami\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akira_Nogami\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am really proud of myself,' Cairess said.\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I did not really care where I came, it was more about doing my best race and feeling like I have fulfilled my potential.\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not control how fit all the other guys are.\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I feel like I ran the best I could have.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In both London marathons I ran, I did not finish the best but this year I was a bit more conservative.\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2778, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999997316265271, \"rank\": 2.6617427696106247e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the first time I have run a real race in the last 2km so I wanted to prove I could finish it off.\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It is the best run I have had by a decent bit.\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just wanted to give myself a chance.\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was my thinking, just try to run as fast as I could until the end.\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Maybe one of them would blow up and I could catch them, but it just so happened that three of them did not blow up.'\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:10,000m runner bizarrely wanders off track at Paris Olympics midway through race  ArrowMORE:Team GB star booed on podium and accused of 'rugby on wheels' tactic  ArrowMORE:Olympic DJ plays 'Imagine' by John Lennon to diffuse beach volleyball row  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3459, \"end\": 3466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imagine_Software\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 9.411165600202579e-13, \"text\": \"Imagine\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imagine_Software\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imagine_Software\"}, {\"begin\": 3471, \"end\": 3482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\", \"score\": 0.9999965171647714, \"rank\": 3.4828474745117896e-06, \"text\": \"John Lennon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lennon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3822, \"end\": 3828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202964147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 4066, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": []}]}"